CatDescriptText: Mr. "Art" Johnson, 2521 Mahon Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 30, 1957, pg. 3 with question: "Does the financial aid, given young married couples by parents, encourage or dissuade the latter's realization of marital responsibilities?" answer reads: "I thing that it dissuades the young couple from assuming its marital responsibilities. The more help the husband and wife get, the less effort will they put forward on their own part."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of "Art" Johnson, wearing hat, eyeglasses, moustache, and light colored double breasted belted trench coat, standing in front of column and shops
